  • Package magpie.csp.diagramdata

    • Class magpie.csp.diagramdata.OnTheFlyPhaseDiagramStatistics extends PhaseDiagramStatistics implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • compoundLookup

          java.util.List<E> compoundLookup
          Lookup tables for elements compound with 1, 2, 3, ... components. Each element of this list contains a sorted map that links each known compound's composition (rounded to exactly match a composition from the PhaseDiagramStatistics.CommonCompositions list to the index of the prototype structure of that compound. Uses a sorted map so that one can lookup all compounds in a particular system quickly.

        • CommonCompositionCopy

          java.util.List<E> CommonCompositionCopy
          Copy of PhaseDiagramStatistics.CommonCompositions used to enable faster lookup from OnTheFlyPhaseDiagramStatistics.getCompositionIndex(double[]).

        • CompositionComparatorCopy

          java.util.Comparator<T> CompositionComparatorCopy
          Comparator for OnTheFlyPhaseDiagramStatistics.CommonCompositionCopy. Must be keep up-to-date with PhaseDiagramStatistics.CompositionComparator.

        • ElemChoices

          java.util.List<E> ElemChoices
          Stores the possible choices of elements when running OnTheFlyPhaseDiagramStatistics.getCompoundVector(int[])

    • Class magpie.csp.diagramdata.PrecomputedPhaseDiagramStatistics extends PhaseDiagramStatistics implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • PhaseDiagram

          java.util.SortedMap<K,V> PhaseDiagram
          Deprecated. 
          For each phase diagram, store list of known compounds and their prototype. Elements in the phase diagram are they key, which are mapped to two integers. x[0] is the index of PhaseDiagramStatistics.CommonCompositions corresponding to the composition of a compound in this diagram, x[1] is the index of the prototype of this compound in the list of prototypes stored for that composition.

        • permutations

          java.util.List<E> permutations
          Deprecated. 
          Precomputed permutations for list of a certain number of entries.
          0 -> 0; 1 -> 01, 10; 2 -> 012, 021, 021, ...
